Exploitation


I generated the SSH key for the exploit. I copied the new key to my directory.


Then I transferred the new key using rsync to the target machine.


And now I have a foothold on the target machine using the new generated SSH key.

Privilege Escalation


Running id shows this user is a member of group fail2ban. Also, ps -auxw shows fail2ban is active. I used this article to escalate my privileges to root. This is achieved by modifying the /etc/fail2ban/action.d/iptables-multiport.conf file and replacing the actionban with the reverse shell.


I started a listener on port 8443 on my machine. After replacing the actionban with my reverse shell, I made an incorrect login with the user root, and gained a reverse shell connection on port 8443.
